$ Oracle: DBMS_SHARED_POOL
@ dbms_shared_pool

`dbms_shared_pool` can be used to
  • display the sizes of objects in the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA/Shared-Pool[shared pool] and
  • mark them for keeping or unkeeping (*pin* und *unpin*) in order to reduce memory fragmentation.


{ Procedures

  table { ll

    `aborted_request_threshold` ☰
    `keep` ☰
    `markhot` ☰
    → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/shared_pool/api/purge[`purge`] ☰ Remove («purge») objects (PL/SQL objects or SQL statements) from the shared pool
    → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/shared_pool/api/sizes[`sizes`] ☰ shows objects that occupy more than a given amount of memory in the shared pool.
    `unkeep` ☰
    `unmarkhot` ☰

  table }

  See also the → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/shared_pool/api/_flag[`flag` parameter].

}

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/db/object_cache` displays pinned objects.

  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA/Shared-Pool

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms
